title: Ford Picks Michigan for Electric-Car Battery Plant With China's CATL
description: Ford Motor Co. and Contemporary Amperex Technology Co. Ltd. plan to build a battery plant in Michigan, according to people familiar with the matter, capping a monthslong search that became mired in geopolitical tensions between the US and China.
author: Gabrielle Coppola

title: More than half of U.S. states are moving to cut your taxes
description: As states' "rainy day funds" reach a record, some state leaders want to eliminate their income tax entirely.
author: Aimee Picchi

title: U.S. states are flush with cash. It's sparking "tax cut fever."
description: Some state officials want to eliminate their income tax entirely. But experts warn of risks from a slowing economy.
author: Aimee Picchi

title: Michigan might send residents $180 checks to combat inflation
description: Michigan Democrats are proposing $180 tax rebates for tax filers. These inflation relief checks are meant to help with the high cost of living.
author: Alicia Adamczyk

title: Whitmer pushes Michigan's highest-ever budget
description: Democratic Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer proposed a $79 billion budget Wednesday — the largest in the state's history — with a focus on school and health spending.
author: Associated Press

title: Whitmer’s ‘implicit bias’ training pushes Michigan health workers to admit bias, ‘get out of your comfort zone
description: An initiative from Democratic Michigan Gov. Gretchen Whitmer forced employees of the state’s Department of Veterans Affairs to take a three-hour "unconscious bias" course.
author: Patrick Hauf

title: California's Newsom slammed after sniping at Gov. Sarah Sanders over Arkansas 'public safety'
description: Governor Gavin Newsom of California, a Democrat, was ripped for attacking Gov. Sarah Huckabee Sanders, in office only a month, for the Razorback State's crime rate.
author: Charles Creitz

title: U.S. Automakers Aim to Make Detroit the Next Silicon Valley
description: U.S. automakers are making large investments in technology. Much of that spending used to go to tech hubs around the country. Now more stays in Michigan.
author: Jake Lingeman

title: Ford to announce new $3.5 billion battery plant in Michigan - sources
description: Ford Motor Co (F.N) is set to announce as soon as Monday it plans to build a $3.5 billion lithium iron phosphate battery plant in Michigan, sources told Reuters.
author: Reuters

title: If not Biden, then who?
description: Democrats are even less sold on Biden running again than Republicans are on Trump. But it matters that the party lacks any potential rival akin to DeSantis.
author: Aaron Blake

title: Democratic governors, seeing rising threats, look beyond their borders
description: Democratic state leaders see a federal government hamstrung to protect rights and see red-state governors pushing to restrict those rights.
author: Dan Balz
